msContents.summary: Incomplete copy of the standard Armenian Church hymnal. Several leaves missing at beginning and end and several mutilated.

supportDesc.extent: 262 leaves ; 140 x 90 (95 x 60) mm, bound to 140 x 92.5 x 60 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in Bolorgir script in black ink.

decoDesc.decoNote: Marginal ornaments in purple, pink and blue, throughout. Rubricated initials and titles throughout.

binding.p: Dark brown leather, blind stamped in floral and geometric designs, over boards. Holes on boards suggest ties or clasps, no longer present.

origin.p: undated, possibly in the 15th or 16th century.

history.provenance: Purchased for the Library from P. Vartooguian, of Adana, approximately 1890 (note on rear board).
